# CURSOR RULES — FOLDERA

## Session Start
- Read: AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, LESSONS_LEARNED.md, CURRENT_STATE.md
- Run `npm run health` first.
- If health shows FAIL, prioritize the first relevant failing row unless the assigned task explicitly targets another proven seam.
- If health is green or warnings-only, continue autonomously.

## Execution Doctrine
- One seam at a time.
- Free tests first. Paid/live proof only at the end.
- Do not reopen closed seams without fresh evidence.
- Do not stop at “improved.” Stop only on win, exact blocker, or final limit.
- Fix the proven seam first. Broaden only if the same failure class is clearly shared.

## Git / Verification
- Push directly to main. Never create branches.
- `npm run build` must pass before every commit.
- Always commit and push when the slice is verified; never defer git to the user unless blocked.
- For live-path or user-facing changes, require one production-like verification before calling the work complete.
- For deterministic harness/test-only changes, local proof is enough until final live verification.

## Architecture Constraints
- Never initialize Supabase or read env vars at top level. Always inside functions.
- `useSession` / `useState` / `useEffect` require `'use client'`.
- Server components use `getServerSession(authOptions)`.
- Frontend uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`.
- Backend uses `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`. Never mix.

## Required Commit Receipt
Every completed task must include:
- what changed
- tests run
- build result
- production/live proof if applicable
- what remains unproven

## Post-Commit Docs
- Update SESSION_HISTORY.md
- Update CURRENT_STATE.md
- Update AUTOMATION_BACKLOG.md when applicable

## Locked Decisions
- Pricing: Free forever + Pro $29/mo
- Tagline: "Finished work, every morning"
- No trial countdown. No credit card for free tier.
- Nicole Vreeland: never a reference or directive target
- Brandon is never the training mechanism
